The paper discusses the ConvAI2 NeurIPS competition, which focuses on improving the state-of-the-art in open-domain chatbots. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of Transformer models, which are a type of deep learning model commonly used in NLP and fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the need to measure performance across sequences of utterances, which could fall under the categories of cs.SD (Sound) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
